article.headline: Lafayette 76, Wagner 70
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jamal Hilliard scored 16 points, Andrew Brown had 15, and Lafayette recovered after blowing a 17-point first-half lead to beat Wagner 76-70 on Friday night. Joey Mundweiler had 22 points for the Seahawks (0-1), who trailed 39-29 at halftime. Mark Porter followed with 16. After Porter opened the scoring with a jumper, the Leopards (1-0) got a pair of 3-pointers by Brown while scoring 19 unanswered points for a 19-2 lead. Porter then scored five points in a 13-4 run that cut the deficit to 23-15 with 10:04 left in the half. Wagner opened the second half with a 13-2 spurt to take a 42-41 advantage on Mundweiler's 3-pointer at with 15:41 remaining. Mundweiler also made another 3 that gave the Seahawks their final lead, 53-52 with 10½ minutes to go, before Lafayette surged into the lead behind Hilliard.
